# Root .env — loaded automatically by Docker Compose for variable substitution.
# Copy to .env and set a real password before running locally:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# This password is only used for the LOCAL dev PostgreSQL containers.
# For Render / Neon deployments the database is managed remotely and this file is irrelevant.

